{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-js","path":"/a-template-for-tech-specs/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"pratham.sh"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"3646e6aa-b260-5f00-8099-11cff4ad0c61","excerpt":"So, let’s all be on the same page first ー It’s  to have no documentation It’s  to have documentation And, it’s  to have documentation which is thorough…","html":"<p>So, let’s all be on the same page first ー</p>\n<ol>\n<li>It’s <code class=\"language-text\">bad</code> to have no documentation</li>\n<li>It’s <code class=\"language-text\">good</code> to have documentation</li>\n<li>And, it’s <code class=\"language-text\">flippin’ amazing</code> to have documentation which is thorough, organised, collaborative, well-written, well-structured, well-articulated and more-well-full-of-productivity-fairy-dust-qualities.</li>\n</ol>\n<hr>\n<p>In this post, I will share a template for writing technical specs. <br>\nThe template outlines lower-level details of the engineering work needed for a feature, service or a small project.</p>\n<h4>Origin story</h4>\n<p>In 2015-17, I worked with the amazing team at <a href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/company/super---your-personal-recruiter/\">Super.jobs (tinder for jobs)</a>. It was the most amazing time I’ve had working. At Super, we came up with this template for writing tech specs.</p>\n<p>I have made a few adjustments over the years while retaining the core document structure. Here is the template -</p>\n<p><strong>Template -</strong><br>\n<a href=\"https://www.notion.so/Tech-Spec-Template-d8f44dd685ad4804bb5a2eddcea62679\">https://www.notion.so/Tech-Spec-Template-d8f44dd685ad4804bb5a2eddcea62679</a></p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 590px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/0df15c75964e7edfcd475f43b8ff402b/7e881/tech-spec-template.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 296.6216216216216%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Tech Spec [Template]\"\n        title=\"Tech Spec [Template]\"\n        src=\"/static/0df15c75964e7edfcd475f43b8ff402b/fcda8/tech-spec-template.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/0df15c75964e7edfcd475f43b8ff402b/12f09/tech-spec-template.png 148w,\n/static/0df15c75964e7edfcd475f43b8ff402b/e4a3f/tech-spec-template.png 295w,\n/static/0df15c75964e7edfcd475f43b8ff402b/fcda8/tech-spec-template.png 590w,\n/static/0df15c75964e7edfcd475f43b8ff402b/efc66/tech-spec-template.png 885w,\n/static/0df15c75964e7edfcd475f43b8ff402b/c83ae/tech-spec-template.png 1180w,\n/static/0df15c75964e7edfcd475f43b8ff402b/7e881/tech-spec-template.png 1521w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p><em><strong>#TODO</strong> Attach a example tech spec.</em></p>","frontmatter":{"title":"Template for writing tech specs","date":"June 14, 2020","description":"I'm sharing a tech specs templates that helps me plan the engineering work. It makes me streamline my thoughts, seek early feedback on approaches and effectively collaborate across teams."}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/a-template-for-tech-specs/","previous":{"fields":{"slug":"/a-case-for-api-client-libraries-in-microservices/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"A case for API client libraries in microservices architecture"}},"next":null}}}